        <h1>Breakfast</h1>
        <h2>Yogurt Parfait</h2>
        <img src="../project/images/yogurt-parfait.jpg" alt="yogurt-parfait" width="200px">
        <table>
            <caption>Recipie</caption>
            <tr>
            <th>Prep Time</th>
            <th>Ingredients</th>
            <th>Optional Ingredients</th>
            </tr>
            <tr class ="evenrow">
                <td>5 minutes</td>
                <td>Granola <br> Yogurt <br> Berries</td>
                <td>Chocolate Chips <br> Honey <br> Peanut Butter</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <ol>
            <li>Grab your favorite cup of yogurt. I happen to love the chobani greek yogurts</li>
            <li>Pour some granola into the yogurt cup. I use the Nature Valley protein + to make sure I get protein in for the day</li>
            <li>Sprinkle some berries on top</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Optional:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Drizzle honey around the top</li>
            <li>Sprinkle in some chocolate chips</li>
            <li>Add a spoonful of peanut butter to add some extra protein! I love the Justin's Maple Almond Butter for this!</li>
        </ol>
        
        
        <h2>Breakfast Sandwich</h2>
        <img src="../project/images/breakfast-sandwich.jpg" alt="breakfast-sandwich" width="200px">
        <table>
            <caption>Recipie</caption>
            <tr>
            <th>Prep Time</th>
            <th>Ingredients</th>
            <th>Optional Ingredients</th>
            </tr>
            <tr class ="evenrow">
                <td>10 minutes</td>
                <td>Bagel <br> Avocado <br> Pre-cooked Bacon <br> Eggs</td>
                <td>Sliced Tomatoes <br> Butter </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <ol>
            <li>Start by putting some oil on a pan and heating it up</li>
            <li>While you're waiting for the pan to heat up, grab out the rest of your ingredients</li>
            <li>Crack an egg onto the pan</li>
            <li>Put your bagel in the Toaster for 4-5 minutes</li>
            <li>While waiting for your bagel to toast, check back on the egg, mix it up if you want it scrambled</li>
            <li>Heat up 2 pieces of pre-cooked bacon in the microwave. Take it out and let it cool for a minute</li>
            <li>By now, your bagel has popped up. Take it out and slice and spread avocado on each side</li>
            <li>Take the bacon and place on one side of the bagel</li>
            <li>Make sure your egg is ready and place it ontop of the bacon.</li>
            <li>Place the other bagel side on top, and you're done!</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Optional:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Add a slice of tomato into the sandwich</li>
            <li>Spread butter onto each side of the bagel before putting the avocado on</li>
        </ol>
